text: Looking for someone to sublet a fully furnished apartment at Hess 16 in Hadar for at least the next month. The apartment is available as of May 10. It has two bedrooms, one of which has a new Ikea daybed (which can be opened into a double) and a new adjustable height desk. There’s a super nice balcony that overlooks the sea. There’s a washing machine, fridge, stove, oven. Also, a piano and guitar are there as well. The caveat is that you’ll have to look after our cat, who is sweet and affectionate. The last subletter unfortunately left a window open and our second cat escaped. It’s been nearly a month and she still hasn’t been found so it’s extra important to take special care of the remaining cat. We are unfortunately stranded in Canada and unable to return for health/visa issues for another month, or whenever Israel begins allowing foreign nationals in. The rent is 3000 nis a month. We will cover the cost of propane, internet, arnona, building council costs, and any food and litter for the cats. Let me know if you or any humans you know and trust are interested. Thanks : )

text:
Hi guys! A beautiful room in the Bat Galim area is available! 🤩💃
In a five-room apartment on the special Bat Galim promenade. 🏝🌅
The room is large and spacious (with a large comfortable double bed, dresser, air conditioner and more), with a super nice walk-in closet and a large window facing the Carmel Ridge. 🌇⛰
In the apartment (first floor), large fully equipped kitchen (oven, stove, microwave, dishwasher, appliances, and more), two bathrooms (equipped with washing machine), air conditioner in every room, huge living room, and lots of good vibes.
Walking distance from the train station, plenty of buses, supermarkets, great sea restaurants, cafes in a young atmosphere, and above all - a meter from the sea and the boardwalk!
In the apartment, two charming and super friendly roommates remain (and an amazing dog), looking for a **female** roommate in the spirit of the house.
Contract until March 2021.
Monthly rent-1,350 NIS, without utilities/arnona.
Immediate entry!

Ashira Dvir‎דירות להשכרה מכירה ושותפים בחיפה
April 11 at 9:13 PM ·
English below
דירת 3 חדרים עם נוף מהמם לים - להשכרה באחוזה! 🌻
מטבח מודרני עם מדיח כלים, מקרר גדול, כיריים גז ותנור בילט אין מוגבה (מצוין למשפחות עם ילדים קטנים). שני חדרי שירותים- שירוקלחת גדולה עם חלון ומקום למכונת כביסה, ושירותי אורחים. מוארת ויפה עם הרבה מקום אחסון (מחסן פרטי של הדירה מתחת לבניין, ארון בילט אין גדול, בוידעם עילי). 3500 ש"ח לחודש.
הדירה ברחוב לינקולן.
צרו קשר עם אביאל 0586296436, או איתן 0587838691 (אנגלית).
פנויה להשכרה מתחילת מאי.
Three bedroomed apartment with spectacular sea view to rent in Ahuza! 🌻
This first-floor apartment in Avraham Lincoln Street is neat and nicely finished with ample storage space. Modern kitchen with dishwasher, spacious fridge/freezer, gas burner and eye level built-in oven. Two bathrooms, one with a bathtub and place for a washing machine.
3500 NIS/month.
Contact Eitan on 0587838691, or Aviel 0586296436.
Available from the 1st of May.

text:
In a few months we will be vacating our paradise in Downtown Haifa after almost 2 years of being there. It’s a 5 room appartment (4 bedrooms, salon) in the most prime location, next to bars and restaurants. It’s a little over 90 sq meters and has 3 balconies. The appartment is fully loaded with every type of furniture you need, just bring your bags and your settled. It’s a perfect place for soldiers just drafting to the army, or even ones released and going to study in the University of Haifa. The appartment suits anyone.
We are looking for 4 people who will move in and treat the place with the same respect that we built it in. If you are interested or know of someone that is interested the please send me a private message to discuss logistics of moving in. We would prefer a group of 4 people, but are flexible with other options.
Also there is no exact move in date yet, we’re also flexible with that too, but sometime around August, September preferred.
Yours truly
-Moshe Aharon 5 Squad

text:
Subletting a 2 rooms, newly renovated flat in Shprinzak. Free between 12.07 and 17.09. Great location for tracks, beach, promenade, train stations and down-town. Great views and breeze, overlooking Vadi Lotem and the sea. Frequent public transportation to anywhere in Haifa, including the Technion and the University. There are also night buses and buses in Shabat.
Because this is my home and it's important for me to have a good subletter that will keep the flat well maintained, I am offering the it for a competitive price of 2,350 a month. That includes rent, wi-fi, all bills and expenses. This is, in the very least, 500 shekels less than what it will actually cost me.
It's a one bedroom, one living-room, characterful open space apartment, with everything one needs for surviving and thriving in Haifa summer time, including air-conditioner in the bedroom, different kitchen appliances (I cook a lot) and a fussball.
If you are interested, pls write me in private.

I am leaving my wonderful apartment in Haifa, and am looking for a replacement! I am looking for someone to takeover my lease from May through September 2019, with an option for extension.
The apartment is a three bedroom apartment on Moriya Boulevard 101A, Haifa, halfway between the Horev and Carmel Center neighborhoods.
The room is completely furnished (see photos.) The apartment has a large living room, a fully equipped kitchen (no need to buy new kitchen supplies), with an oven and gas stove, and one and a half bathrooms. We also have a washing machine in the apartment.
